Y rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":null,"pe_percentile":null,"median_pe":null,"earnings_yield_pct":null,"pb":null,"ev_ebitda":null,"quality_score":null,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":null,"peg":null,"cheapness":{"status":"na","read":null},"expectations":null,"cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[86.36,86.36,86.36,86.36,86.36,86.36,86.36,86.36,86.36,86.36,86.36,84.65],"latest_pct":84.65,"chg_1y_pp":-1.71},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[1.14,1.14,1.15,1.08,1.11,1.09,1.01,0.98,0.93,0.97,0.98,1.16],"latest_pct":1.16,"chg_1y_pp":0.18},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[2.02,1.63,1.15,0.89,1.08,1.08,1.24,1.34,1.45,1.48,1.54,2.89],"latest_pct":2.89,"chg_1y_pp":1.55},"Publi